      <h2>What to Look for in a Beginner Harmonium</h2>
      <p>Tuning quality is the most important factor — a poorly tuned harmonium trains your ear incorrectly. Look for 9-stop models with 2 sets of reeds for good tone variety. Standard 39 keys (3.25 octaves) is sufficient for all beginner and most intermediate playing. Portability matters if you plan to carry it to kirtan or practice sessions. Budget minimum Rs 5000 to avoid very cheap instruments with unreliable tuning.</p>

      <h2>Top Pick: Bina No. 17 Deluxe — Rs 8500 to Rs 11000</h2>
      <p>Best overall for beginners. Bina harmoniums have been made since 1936 and are the gold standard in India. The No. 17 Deluxe offers excellent tuning stability consistent build quality and 2.5 octaves with 9 stops. It weighs about 8 kg. The higher price is justified by significantly longer life and better tuning retention compared to cheaper alternatives.</p>

      <h2>Value Pick: Paloma BH-39 — Rs 6000 to Rs 8000</h2>
      <p>Best value for money. Good tuning out of the box lightweight at 6.5 kg and widely available across India. The reeds may need checking after 6 months of daily use but overall an excellent choice for most beginners. Highly recommended as the practical choice for students who are budget-conscious but serious about learning.</p>

      <h2>Budget Pick: Radhe Krishna Portable — Rs 4000 to Rs 5500</h2>
      <p>Acceptable for casual learning and kirtan use on a tight budget. Tuning is adequate but may drift more frequently than premium models. Buy from a reputable music store that will check tuning before sale. Sufficient for learning the basics but plan to upgrade within 1-2 years if you continue seriously.</p>

      <h2>Where to Buy in India</h2>
      <p>Music stores are best — you can test instruments check tuning and return if defective. Look for established music stores in your city especially in music hubs like Delhi's Darya Ganj, Mumbai's Falkland Road, or Kolkata's Rabindra Sarani. Online options on Amazon.in and Flipkart are available — buy only from verified sellers with return policies. Always check tuning before finalizing any purchase.</p>

